abstract: Jessie Diggins and Caitlin Gregg take silver and bronze in the 10-kilimeter freestyle event at the Nordic skiing world championships, becoming first Americans to win major championship medals in cross-country skiing.
lead_paragraph: Jessie Diggins and Caitlin Gregg won the first major championship medals for American women in long-distance cross-country skiing racing.
snippet: Jessie Diggins and Caitlin Gregg won the first major championship medals for American women in long-distance cross-country skiing racing.
